cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic segmentation using deep neural networks, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new network architecture and training method, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of random walks and similarity estimation also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the Pascal VOC and Pascal Context datasets, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
